                        L.H. SEAMAN, JUVENILE DEPT.
                            <lb/>
                        W.H. MURRAY, RELIGIOUS DEPT.
                            <lb/>
                        
                        TELEPHONE ALGONQUIN 2100
                    </hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>December 6, 1927.</dateline>
                
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>St. Louis Post-Dispatch,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri.</addrLine>
                </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am glad to learn from your letter of November 27 that there is continued and increasing interest in your cycle. Mr. Seaver is now away, but upon his return I shall be glad to bring to his attention the question of advertising and also the question of using Dr. House for a time on the road.</p>
                
                <p>We are now just about ready to proceed with <hi rend="caps">THE SONG OF THE INDIAN WARS</hi>. However, we need definite information as to the extent of the Notes in order to make our publishing order. Will you, therefore, be good enough either to send us the Notes for estimate here or estimate yourself the number of pages that they would make on the basis of the Notes given in the other book? And, will you kindly let us know also whether the front matter will be different from that found in the regular edition or whether there should be changes of any sort?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours very truly,</salute>
                    <signed>J.F. Brown
                    THE MACMILLAN COMPANY,
                    Editorial Department.</signed>
                
                    <note>JFB.MC</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note place="margin" type="recipient">I've given this information, allowing for matter you may add. Jno.</note>
                
            </div1>
